Gold Draws Net $4.8 Billion in New Investments, BlackRock Says

-- B y   T o n y   C .   D r e i b u s
-- 
2011-12-08T17:26:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/gold-draws-net-4-8-billion-in-new-investments-blackrock-says.html
Gold generated a net $4.8 billion in
new investments in November, outperforming all other asset
categories, said BlackRock Inc.  Gold inflows totaled $3.5 billion in the U.S. and $1.3
billion in  Europe , New York-based BlackRock, the worldâ€™s biggest
asset manager, said in a report. Investors moved money into
commodities including gold from equities, which had outflows of
$8.5 billion last month, mainly from North American and European
